topic: History Workflow Series ("Literary Movements and physicists explorative search")

goals.1: Who invented the theory of relativity? (return the IRI and the label of the inventor).
goals.3: Identify the BGP for Nobel Prize
goals.4: Consider physicists born in Europe. For each european country return the number of physicists who won the Nobel Prize in Physics (the result set must be a list of triples country IRI, label and #physicists).
goals.5: Return the countries which won at least once all the type of Nobel Prizes with the people born there. (the result set must be a list of couples country IRI and label).
goals.6: Amongst the physicists who won the Nobel Prize in Physics, find who had discovered or invented at least 3 things (the result set must be a list of triples physicist IRI, label and #discoveries ).
goals.7: Amongst the physicists who won the Nobel Prize in Physics, find who taught in the university of his/her city of birth (the result set must be a list of elements of the form physicist IRI, label, university IRI and label).
